# NETWORK KEY COMMANDS

-List and modify interfaces on the host IP, like network cards for example
ip link

-List IP addresses assigned to those interfaces
ip addr

-Set IP addresses on the interfaces, calling the interface names
ip addr add IP-ADDRESS dev ethos
sudo ip addr add 172.16.239.10/24 dev eth0

-View the routing table
ip route

-Add entries into the routing table
ip route add TARGET-NETWORK-IP-ADDRESS via LOCAL-GATEWAY-IP-ADDRESS

-Check if IP forwarding is enabled on a host
cat /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward

--It can be used to query a hostname from a DNS server
nslookup www.google.com

-It is another useful tool to test DNS name resolution, it returns more details in a similar form as is stored
dig
